defaultExecutive Summary
default&#xa0;
defaultThe Ministry of
default Defence should undertake to pay full tort damages for all deaths and injuries sustained during active operations
default on a no-fault basis
default, as the 
defaultquid pro quo
default for removing the right to sue in 
defaulttort (e.g. 
defaultfor 
defaultnegligence
default)
default.  (Crown immunity can be revived by the S
defaultecretary of State’s making a suitable Order under the 
defaultCrown Proceedings (Armed Forces) Act 1987
default; it has previously been suggested that this should be done to 
defaultreverse 
defaultSmith v. Ministry of Defence
default to avert that decision’s likely pernicious influence on milit
defaultary effectiveness.)
